$ SAS: automatic macro variables
@ automatic macro variables

Automatic variables start with either `&af` or `&sys`.

→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/variables/automatic/devic

→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/variables/automatic/syslibrc

→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/variables/automatic/sysscp-sysscpl[&sysscp and &sysscpl]

→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/proc/sql/sqlobs

{ Date and time related automatic macro variables

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/variables/automatic/date-time.sas||

  Note: these variables record the time when the session was started. They then don't change anymore. The actual current time
  must be deteremined with `time()`
  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/variables/automatic/time-sessionstart-current.sas||


}
{ Last dataset created #last-dataset-created

  The name of the last → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/data-sets[data set] is stored in `&syslast`:
  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/variables/automatic/syslast.sas||

}
{ Related to the host

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/variables/automatic/hostname-etc.sas||

}
{ Memory structure sizes

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/variables/automatic/memory-structure-sizes.sas||

}
{ Related to processess

  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/variables/automatic/process.sas||

}
{ Show all(?) automatic macro variables

  All automatic variables can be shown with → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/statements/put[`%put _automatic_;`]. 


  Here's a list of some automatic variables:
  gh|about-SAS|/macro-processor/automatic-macro-variables.sas||

}

{ _SASWS_

  In SAS Studio, `&_SASWS_` references the home directory. 

}

